2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the performance comparison of cell-free massive MIMO operation with and without downlink training, considering different network densities. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper considers the performance improvement provided by max-min fairness power control in the downlink. This is a topic of interest in systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper discusses the net throughput performance of cell-free massive MIMO systems, which is relevant to multimedia applications. 
5. cs.COM (Computers and Society): While the paper does not directly address societal issues related to computing, it may have implications for the design and deployment of wireless communication systems, which could impact society.
